Configure AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) Role for Voice

When using Service Cloud Voice with Partner Telephony from Amazon Connect, you must create a role with the correct policy information. Then, specify the ARN for your IAM role in Amazon Connect when setting up Voice in Salesforce.

To create your IAM role, follow these steps:

Log in to your AWS account and select Roles.
Create a role with Account ID 793525387755 as the trusted entity type.
Create an inline policy by pasting the SCVProvisioningPolicy.json policy into the JSON tab.
Replace occurrences of <AWS_ACCOUNT_ID> and <BYOAC_CUSTOM_S3_BUCKET> with your values.
Name it ProvisioningPolicy.

After creating the IAM role, use the role ARN value when setting up Voice in Salesforce.

title: Configure AWS IAM Role for Service Cloud Voice
